# C SOP

- Target C11 or project standard; enable warnings and treat as errors when the build supports it.
- Check every allocation return; pair every acquire with release (memory, fds, locks).
- Prefer explicit error paths; use `goto cleanup` for multi-step init/teardown when the repo already does.
- No undefined behavior: validate lengths, bounds, and null at API boundaries; avoid implicit truncations.
- Headers: include guards or `#pragma once`; keep `.h` declarations minimal; include what you use in `.c`.
- Naming: match project convention (`snake_case` typical); static for file scope unless exported.
- Concurrency: document threading assumptions; use project mutex/lock primitives consistently.
- Tests: unit tests via project runner (`make test`, `ctest`, custom harness); valgrind/ASan when available.
- Build: match Makefile/CMake; do not hand-edit generated artifacts.
- Security: no unchecked `strcpy`/`sprintf`; bounded copies; sanitize external input sizes.
